    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A rare lead compound, a transparent to pale white mineral in the monoclinic system. It was first identified in the lead-antimony vein at the southwestern end of Bounds Cliff, Cornwall by Cornish mineral collector Richard A. Barstow. It has also been found as a corrosion product on lead artifacts.</Note_Text>
